Crimes Against Persons rate per 1,000 population and percentage change in that rate
Reporting Frequency: Annually (Calendar Year)S.B.1.b Crimes against PropertyDefinition: This measure is how many crimes against property occurred per 1,000 population in Austin.Calculation Method: We calculated this measure using the formula: Total Number of crimes divided by the population of Austin in 2019 divided by 1,000.Data Collection Process: Number of offenses are tracked by APD and validated by the FBI. This measure is on a 2 year lag. Measure Target Calculation: N/AFrequency Measure is Reported: Annually (Calendar Year)S.B.1.c Crimes against SocietyDefinition: This measure is how many crimes against society occurred per 1,000 population in Austin.Calculation Method: We calculated this measure using the formula: Total Number of crimes divided by the population of Austin in 2019 divided by 1,000.Data Collection Process: Number of offenses are tracked by APD and validated by the FBI. This measure is on a 2 year lag.Measure Target Calculation: N/AFrequency Measure is Reported: Annually (Calendar Year)
